TouchableOpacity
1. A wrapper for making views respond properly to touches.

2. Using with the style to make it work like a interactive button
<TouchableOpacity
    style={styles.button}
    onPress={onPress}
>
....
button: {
    alignItems: "center",
    backgroundColor: "#DDDDDD",
    padding: 10
  }

3. Add inPress function to enable the button to trigger function
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  const onPress = () => setCount(prevCount => prevCount + 1);

4. function:
 - onPress: when pressing on, the event trigger instantly
 - onPressOut: when release the buttton, the event trigger